It’s not about building a wall.
It’s time to build the will, even more than the wall.
We have never had such a severe and blatant invasion through migration last this long without the president implementing a plan to shut it down.
Trump can halt all immigration and cross-border commerce for any reason if he determines it’s in the national interest.
Congress can never write a statute more unambiguous and granting the president more unconditional power to shut off even legal immigration than 212(f).